97
00:06:47,866 --> 00:06:55,730
[SPEAKER_02]: But I also wanted to lift a potential sort of interactive that Diane had shared when we had a conversation.

98
00:06:57,939 --> 00:07:16,554
[SPEAKER_02]: in sort of inviting folks, acknowledging that we have as little time as we do, acknowledging that people are as busy as they are, but inviting just the community and especially our students to kind of think about their thoughts on where Medford is as a community and city right now.

99
00:07:16,674 --> 00:07:24,420
[SPEAKER_02]: And then maybe we thought about inviting people to write a letter to King or write a letter in the name of King's tenants around Medford.

100
00:07:25,441 --> 00:07:28,563
[SPEAKER_02]: how they're feeling given our current climate.

101
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:32,666
[SPEAKER_02]: And we thought that might be kind of like an easy push through Dr. Edward.

102
00:07:34,547 --> 00:07:37,409
[SPEAKER_02]: But beyond that, we didn't feel like we had capacity.

103
00:07:37,770 --> 00:07:39,871
[SPEAKER_02]: And I also don't want to misspeak.

104
00:07:39,911 --> 00:07:44,834
[SPEAKER_02]: So Kelly and Diane, if I'm saying something that's off, totally check me.

