110
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:06,729
[SPEAKER_07]: I guess that's really what I'm asking.

111
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:17,260
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, no, I was just wanting to share the kind of iterations of discussion that we had from the point of considering an author discussion through until now.

112
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:23,990
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm sorry, I'm still a little confused.

113
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:30,974
[SPEAKER_07]: The author that you told me about, is that the person, is that the direction that we were moving towards or did something change?

114
00:08:31,014 --> 00:08:34,435
[SPEAKER_07]: I just want to make sure that I didn't miss anything.

115
00:08:34,455 --> 00:08:43,821
[SPEAKER_07]: Because I felt like you were working off the plan of the speaker series and the book.

116
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:45,602
[SPEAKER_07]: No?

117
00:08:46,726 --> 00:08:48,247
[SPEAKER_02]: So I mean, initially, yes.

118
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:48,687
[SPEAKER_02]: Right.

119
00:08:48,747 --> 00:08:54,731
[SPEAKER_02]: But I think like the larger feeling, the larger sense was that like there's not enough time.

120
00:08:56,032 --> 00:09:04,578
[SPEAKER_02]: People felt pulled in too many directions and also maybe like not enough appreciation from the side of the city, given that this event does take as much work as it does.

121
00:09:05,839 --> 00:09:15,125
[SPEAKER_02]: And it has felt hard to have folks reach out in support suddenly this year when it really just didn't happen other years, even though we bent over backwards to ask.

122
00:09:16,145 --> 00:09:29,797
[SPEAKER_02]: So yeah, there was a point when we wanted to host a discussion around the sword and the shield and that book is heavy and we didn't want to host something that felt performative.

123
00:09:29,857 --> 00:09:35,222
[SPEAKER_02]: So giving people less than a week to chew through it and actually read it didn't feel that savory, I guess.

124
00:09:36,223 --> 00:09:40,366
[SPEAKER_02]: And so in place of that, when the three of us had a discussion,

125
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:58,231
[SPEAKER_02]: was the possibility of inviting people to write a letter combining the current climate in Medford to like center our reality right now, but keeping in mind King's tenets to also pull in the kind of spirit of the day.

126
00:09:58,251 --> 00:10:02,833
[SPEAKER_02]: So that was something that came up, but that is a piece that came up before

127
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:19,208
[SPEAKER_02]: conversation around the work that EMBRACE is doing and this like really brilliant idea of leaning into what will be live streamed on Monday and having Medford join an understandably kind of larger discussion for City of Boston and Metro Boston.

128
00:10:20,289 --> 00:10:27,015
[SPEAKER_02]: So just like multiple steps of where energy and capacity has potentially lent itself.

129
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:28,497
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah.

130
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,780
[SPEAKER_02]: And again, jump in.

131
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,242
[SPEAKER_03]: And time just felt very short.

132
00:10:35,102 --> 00:10:50,151
[SPEAKER_03]: So I think we want to just be, you know, leading into next year, we're going to be much more prepared and have a longer lead time for planning and just pulling, you know, because I had some conversations with stakeholders, and it just felt like we were getting to be a week out.

133
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:57,775
[SPEAKER_03]: And I think that if we start thinking about this late, you know, even late summer, early fall this year,

134
00:10:58,645 --> 00:11:00,948
[SPEAKER_03]: we're going to be set up for great success.

135
00:11:01,249 --> 00:11:05,935
[SPEAKER_03]: And I would love for us to pivot to Black History Month.

136
00:11:06,275 --> 00:11:13,705
[SPEAKER_03]: And I have a concrete idea that I'd love to offer and share when the time is right, that I think we could be successful on and see what folks think.

