176
00:12:48,343 --> 00:12:49,684
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you.

177
00:12:51,165 --> 00:12:56,748
[SPEAKER_03]: So as you all know, I've been a longtime volunteer at Royal House and Slave Quarters.

178
00:12:57,649 --> 00:13:09,656
[SPEAKER_03]: And Belinda Sutton and her powerful petition that really centers on civil rights and human rights is dated

179
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:15,704
[SPEAKER_03]: on Valentine's Day, February 14th, 1783.

180
00:13:16,004 --> 00:13:20,848
[SPEAKER_03]: So this Valentine's Day will be the 240th commemorative year.

181
00:13:20,948 --> 00:13:35,181
[SPEAKER_03]: And when I think about the work of Dr. King, I think about, you know, the people who lived and worked at Royal House and slave quarters and were really, you know, activists and, you know,

182
00:13:36,162 --> 00:13:46,346
[SPEAKER_03]: leaders of the very early American civil rights movement, it should be just this really great point of pride for us in Medford, because it's part of our origin story.

183
00:13:47,046 --> 00:13:54,249
[SPEAKER_03]: And so I would love to see us as a human rights commission host

184
00:13:55,373 --> 00:14:11,310
[SPEAKER_03]: an activity there to kind of lift up Belinda and the people, you know, from there, like Prince Hall, well, Fortune Howard, you know, who was part of Prince Hall's movement, and have people really reflect and think about

185
00:14:12,507 --> 00:14:24,073
[SPEAKER_03]: the meaning of Belinda's petition and its relevance to today, because it uses a lot of really great rhetoric around freedom and democracy from the Declaration of Independence.

186
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:39,081
[SPEAKER_03]: And then maybe have a service activity that's fun and exciting for families in the same way that Kelly wants to get schools involved with the Embrace Boston.

187
00:14:40,381 --> 00:14:41,422
[SPEAKER_03]: Like how about

188
00:14:42,212 --> 00:15:00,539
[SPEAKER_03]: you know, we could have someone do a talk about the importance of Belinda and her powerful petition, you know, in the lead up to Valentine's Day, and then have a service activity around make Valentines for the local nursing homes.

189
00:15:00,639 --> 00:15:10,142
[SPEAKER_03]: I'd be completely happy to deliver them or affix them to a poster board, you know, and bring, you know, to the nursing homes in Medford.

190
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:11,263
[SPEAKER_03]: Belinda was,

